review:
Shogun 2 is great;
Simple, yet complex gameplay;
Great presentation.

A haiku summing up my feels on Shogun 2:

Our clan will rise up;
Will unify the island;
Damn, foiled again.

(For real though. This is one of my favorite Total War games and one of the more difficult ones I've played (especially with the rebalancing and extra features the Radious mod has to offer). Out of all the Total War games of recent memory, Shogun 2 was probably the best polished, from release to the last official supporting patch and its two expansions. Also, those epic siege battles though.)

As a fan of all the Total War saga, I must admit that shogun 2 it's one of the best (and one of the most difficult) and I love in particular "Fall of the Samurai" (the artillery there is simply AMAZING).
Pros:
-Graphic (both campaign's map and battles) gorgeus;
-Battles quite smooth and fluent (more than rome 2 actually);
-Samurai! (ok, this is just because I love Japanese history and culture);
-The skill system for generals and agents, which is even better in FotS;

Cons:
-The units are almost all the same for each clan (I would like to see more special and unique units);
-The size of the map can quickly make the game a bit boring;

Anyway, one of my best games so far.  9/10 (10/10 for FotS, absolutely).
